Three police officers attached to Divisional Police station, Udung Uko Local Government Area of Akwa Ibom State have sustained fatal injuries in an attempt to repel an attack by gunmen who invaded the station on Saturday, July 3, 2021. The hoodlums it was gathered stormed the station in a Toyota Sienna vehicle and opened fire on officers and men at the station. A source from the area who pleaded anonymity said, ”the unknown gunmen shot sporadically last night(Saturday) at the police divisional headquarters Udung Uko. Again, gunmen raze police station, kill two officers in Anambra “The gallant Police officers on duty tried to repel the attack. Three policemen sustained fatal degrees of injuries resulting from the attack and are receiving treatment in a hospital.” The source added that Udung Uko was no longer safe and demanded the attention of relevant authorities to forestall any future occurrence. The Police Public Relations Officer in the State, Odiko Macdon who confirmed the incident to our correspondent said no life was lost during the attack. The PPRO lauded the officers on duty for their vigilance and gallantry in repelling the attack by the hoodlums. “An attempt was made at our facility in Udung Uko local government area of Akwa Ibom state but our men repelled that attack. There was no casualty. The vigilance of our men on duty led to the foiling of the attack. “Armed men came into the station in a Sienna Toyota car with an unknown number and opened fire and our men repelled them and they zoomed off.” He added that security has been beefed up at the station and investigations ongoing.